From Jerry Lotto Subject Re where to put your helmet On Apr GMT Ryan Cousineau said CB DON'T BE SO STUPID AS TO LEAVE YOUR HELMET ON THE SEAT WHERE IT CAN CB FALL DOWN AND GO BOOM Ryan Another good place for your helmet is your mirror I kid you This is very bad Helmets have two major impact absorbing a hard outer shell and a closed cell foam impact Most helmets lose their protective properties because the inner liner compacts over time long before the outer shell is damaged or delaminates from Hurt tested helmets for many years following his landmark study and has estimated that a helmet can lose up to of it's effectiveness from inner liner I have a video he produced that discusses this phenomenon in Puncture compression of the type caused by mirrors sissy bars and other relatively sharp objects is the worst Even when the comfort liner is unaffected dents and holes in the foam can seriously degrade the effectiveness of a If you are in the habit of parking your lid on the mirrors I suggest you look under the comfort liner at the condition of the If it is significantly damaged or missing replace the Jerry Lotto MSFCI HOGSSC BCSO AMA DoD Chemistry Harvard It's my Harley and I'll ride if I want